<div class="row">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="col-md-4"> <img src="~/images/EIB-small.jpg" /></div>
        <div class="col-md-4"> <h1><b>Engineering on Display</b></h1></div>
        <div class="col-md-4"><img style="width:50%; height:50%" src="~/images/Siemens.png" /></div>
    </div>
</div>
<hr style="border:1px solid black;" />
<div align="center">
    <p class="textMain">
        Welcome to the engineering on display (EoD) of UAA. This is a part of an effort to rasise
        awarness and knowledge about the energy useage of even a single building in the modern world.
        As part of a collaberative effor between UAA and Siemens this display gives you a view into
        the quanitiy of electricity, natural gas and water that this building takes, as well as being
        able to view the fluctuations in this over time.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="square">
                <p class="textInstructionHead">step 1</p>
                <p class="textInstructionBody">Select icon from side bar to display information desired</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="square">
                <p class="textInstructionHead">step 2</p>
                <p class="textInstructionBody">Select time period and usage/ demand to display graph <br/><br/>Usage - total amount since the building opened<br/>Demand - amount used at any one time</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="square">
                <p class="textInstructionHead">step 3</p>
                <p class="textInstructionBody">Scroll to see the graph change with time</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>




